RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 1 330 Y Dirt CR: 75. Allowance Purse 12000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FDD FAST MAN unchallenged and was kept under a confident hand ride. TIMBERS MOON raced evenly. TIMBER BUNNY lacked the kick needed.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 64. Claiming Purse 9000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $3,500. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $4,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHRIS'S COMMAND pressed the pace from the three path, was roused entering the stretch then drew clear under intermittent encouragement. CHARMING VINTAGE stalked the early pacesetters while four to five wide, asked to quicken in the final turn, rallied three wide then dueled through the stretch for second. BEAUGATTI saved ground heading into the far turn, drove between then was out-finished in the stretch duel for second. AMEER rated well off the pace inside, and passed a tiring rival deep stretch. SOMETHIN HAPPENIN vied inside for the lead, and faltered in the stretch. MAMA'S PROUD JOKE offered little.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 3 1M Dirt CR: 74. Claiming Purse 10500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR ALBERTA BREDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $6,000 (Lesser Claim ing Races For $3,500 (AB $4,500) At Century Mile Not Considered In Eligibility). Alberta Bred Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WYE CROSS raced from the back of the field, advanced inside in the far turn then shifted outside at the head of the lane, gained on the leader steadily and was along in time to score. INDEPENDENCE NEIGH raced four wide into the opening turn, rated a slim lead outside of ALL THAT GOLD, dueled through the final turn, moved clear entering the stretch, and was rundown deep stretch. FULL VELOCITY settled along the rail, chased five wide on the last turn, and showed little further. ALL THAT GOLD sent to the lead, contested the pace inside of INDEPENDENCE NEIGH, was unable to move on with rival after the quarter pole, and stopped. MAJOR SHEPARD sat mid-pack and lacked a bid. IGNITE THE MOON was reserved off the leaders and tired early.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 4 1M Dirt CR: 68. Maiden Special Weight Purse 20000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HANDSOME HENRY raced three wide leaving the opening turn, shifted out to the five path in the backstretch, chased in the far turn, advanced quickly outside then dueled in the final sixteenth and inched clear. AL REICHERT raced four wide entering the backstretch, rallied under light handling, hooked up with rival midstretch but was outfinished. DADDY'S PEPPER went four wide leaving the first turn, angled inside to the rail to give chase, gained closer contention in the final turn, moved up menacingly but was outkicked. COOL DOMINION saved ground inside, lodged an all-out bid entering the stretch and passed a tiring rival deep stretch. LOLLIPOP KID showed the way through the backstetch, drew away with good margins but so those rapidly shrink after passing the quarter pole, and gave way in the stretch. CANADIAN AUTHORITY rated off the pace while four wide, and had no response when called upon. TRAPEZE never reached contention. AL REICHERT is hereby disqualified and declared unplaced due to a positive test.

ENTRY.NAME: Cool Dominion
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, all out bid, passed tiring

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 5 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 85. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 19500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING $17,500. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $17,500. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $2 2,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KYSTONE rated well off the early pacesetters, went in pursuit of the leaders in the far turn, drove four wide off the last turn, struck the front moved clear and finished on a light hand ride. CLANCY'S PISTOL hesitated at the start, advanced quickly in the far turn, was brushed at the head of the lane, closed gradually improving position late. THESHACK hurried outside, contended the pace outside of GODGUNSNCOUNTY, was quickly overtaken at the quarter pole, kept under urging through the stretch and held on for show. MACHINE settled in the four path, and lodged a late mild bid. SILVERFOOT saved ground from along the rail in second flight, was brushed near the three-sixteenth pole, kept on evenly through the drive under urging, and missed. SIMMS failed to be a factor. TACOFLAVOREDKISSES settled five wide, and lacked a bid. GODGUNSNCOUNTRY away alertly, drew away from the field while in a dueling match with THESHACK, and had nothing left in reserve. STEWARDS INQUIRY- The Stewards conducted an inquiry into the start of the race involving CLANCY'S PISTOL. After review it was determined that CLANCY'S PISTOL did receive a fair start and made no change.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 78. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 19500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, OR RESTRICTED STAKES RACE IN ALBERTA OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING $17,000. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $17,000. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $22,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUNBIRD broke inward bumping into VANTASTICCANAVERAL, hurried up inside of FOUR O SIX CREED to press the early pace, dueled through the final turn, gained an advantage in the stretch and held under steady pressure late. FOUR O SIX CREED disputed the early pace outside of SUNBIRD, was unable to continue to match strides at the head of the lane, but continued to keep the pressure late stretch. KAUAI DAN broke outward into SHURAZ, chased from the rail, and lacked the kick needed. BIG BAD INTAGLIO settled in stride from the five path, exchanged brushes inside of READYTOTAPNSING, and was unable to improve position through the drive. READYTOTAPNSING fanned three wide leaving the backstretch, came together with BIG BAD INTAGLIO at the head of the lane and lacked the bid that was needed. SMART CAT chased wide through the backstretch, angled to the four path, and faded. VANTASTICCANAVERAL sandwiched leaving, chased briefly, and dropped back. SHURAZ squeezed out at the start, and was unable to recover any ground throughout. JOCKEY OBJECTION- An objection lodged by the rider of SHURAZ against the rider of SUNDBIRD alleging interference at the start was not allowed after review of the film.

ENTRY.NAME: Kauai Dan
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke outward, bumped, chased, lacked kick

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 7 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 84. Claiming Purse 13500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WHERE'S THE GOLD tracked outside through the backstretch, went five to six wide in the far turn, responded to urging at the three-sixteenth pole, and closed gamely to get by with time. MUCHO MAGIC tracked three wide, dropped back through the far turn, lodged a rail bid, and was along deep stretch for to score place honors. JULIUS THE GREAT sat just off the pace while four wide, overtook the lead at the head of the stretch and was caught late. ALONGTHEWATCHTOWER was under a snug hold into the backstretch, fanned five wide, chased outside nearing the quarter pole, and lacked the closing response needed while under steady urging. DUNE D'ORO chased inside, shifted out entering the stretch and bid belatedly. TAPIT TO THE WIRE experienced traffic in the backstretch, was roused sharply entering the lane, shifted inside and came up empty for the drive. KOVACS tracked four to five wide, and faded steadily. FAST EH led the field into the backstretch, had no response when challenged, and stopped. PRESS GANG chased outside, lacking running room leaving the backstretch, and was roused to no avail.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 8 6F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 10000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Lesser Claiming Races No t Considered In Eligibility). Alberta Bred Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OUT FRONT showed good speed outside early, emerged the leader leaving the backstretch, responded to CARRIE'S SUCCESS heading into the lane, and drew clear in the final sixteenth. CAPA BELLA broke in bumping into WAVESINTHEOCEAN, chased outside, and closed steadily outside getting up late for second. CARRIE'S SUCCESS brushed leaving then hustled up to contest the early pace, dueled in the final turn and weakened late stretch. DAZZLING CHIC hustled away, and lacked a kick that was needed. KISSABLE U away well then vied three wide, chased the leaders into the final turn, and flattened out. THERUFFSIDEOFEXHI assumed a tracking position, and came up empty in the drive. LITTLE ROSALYN offered little. WHEELSUPINTHIRTY chased three-wide leaving the backstretch, and gave way. KERIK was outrun. WAVESINTHEOCEAN was bumped then started to buck away from the gate, and was distanced.
